The article discusses the proposed budget plans from Republicans in Congress and the upcoming budget proposal from the author. The Republicans' proposals would add $3 trillion to the national debt over 10 years. However, the author's budget will not increase taxes for individuals earning less than $400,000 a year, which has been the case for the past 2 years. The author's budget aims to invest in America, reduce costs, and protect and strengthen Social Security and Medicare. Additionally, it plans to cut the deficit by $2 trillion over 10 years.